<item>
            <title>[WICKET-4136] component without close tag fails with &quot;Unable to find close tag for&quot; if it is the last componet on page</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-4136</link>
                <project id="12310561" key="WICKET">Wicket</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;A simple page with the following markup will fail:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;html&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;img wicket:id=&quot;photo&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/html&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;but this one will work:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;html&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;img wicket:id=&quot;photo&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;span wicket:id=&quot;label&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/html&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I believe the bug is in the code below:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;	public MarkupFragment(final IMarkupFragment markup, final int startIndex)&lt;br/&gt;
	{&lt;br/&gt;
		if (...) &lt;/p&gt;
		{
		   ...
		}&lt;br/&gt;
		else if (startTag.hasNoCloseTag())&lt;br/&gt;
		{&lt;br/&gt;
			for (endIndex = startIndex + 1; endIndex &amp;lt; markup.size(); endIndex++)&lt;br/&gt;
			{&lt;br/&gt;
				MarkupElement elem = markup.get(endIndex);&lt;br/&gt;
				if (elem instanceof ComponentTag)  // It looks for another component tag to indicate the end of the body, but fails if it is the last one&lt;br/&gt;
				{
					endIndex--;
					break;
				}&lt;br/&gt;
			}&lt;br/&gt;
		}&lt;br/&gt;
		else&lt;br/&gt;
		{		   ...		}

&lt;p&gt;		if (endIndex &amp;gt;= markup.size())&lt;/p&gt;
		{
			throw new MarkupException(&quot;Unable to find close tag for: &apos;&quot; + startTag.toString() +
				&quot;&apos; in &quot; + getRootMarkup().getMarkupResourceStream().toString());
		}
&lt;p&gt;	}&lt;/p&gt;</description>
